                  </span></div><br><div class="comment">
                  <span class="c00">Any app that asks for your location can and will track you. This is so lucrative that Foursquare pivoted the whole company around the concept of location data as a service (<a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;enterprise.foursquare.com&#x2F;" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;enterprise.foursquare.com&#x2F;</a>).<p>Fortunately, you just need to revoke the permission (or don&#x27;t grant it in the first place) if you want to avoid being tracked. If you&#x27;re concerned about this, I&#x27;d definitely suggest doing a quick check of the apps that track your location and disable the permission in the ones that you distrust.<span>
